rush default

  Set a default repository.
  
  This command adds (or updates) a repository named `default` to the
  configuration file, and copies the path from the provided repo.

[1mUsage:[0m
  rush default REPO
  rush default --help | -h

[1mOptions:[0m
  --help, -h
    Show this help

[1mArguments:[0m
  REPO
    Repository name.

[1mExamples:[0m
  rush default sample
